<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-562-935  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 562 935.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Lasers andamp; Optronics  Oct 1990 v9 n10 p16(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Sensored composites reach for their potential.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Weiss, Richard.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Two high-strength optical fibers are in commercial production.andO;One is a single-crystal sapphire; the other is a specially coatedsilica fiber that has a breaking strength that approaches onemillion pounds psi.andP;  Sensored composites (SC) is a newsubcategory; the essence of this subcategory is the method ofusing special fibers for strengthening and detailed opticalsensing.andP;  A piezoelectric sheet of transparent quartz can beattached between the LED and the coherent bundle to obtain thetwo-dimensional array at a specific point along the length of thecomposite.andP;  Doping the glass fibers with a thermochromic liquidcrystal provides temperature sensing.andP;  The rotation inpolarization can be related by using crossed polarizers.andP;  Otherstructural members can be combined with the SC.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Fiber OpticsResearch and DevelopmentTemperatureArrays.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>